# dbt Secondary Repo Sync

dbt Cloud reads from `responsum-team/dbtproject`, NOT from `elixirrjob1/cursorskills`.
Pushing to main is not enough — you must also sync to the secondary repo or dbt Cloud will run old code.

## When to sync

After any commit that touches `dbt_project/drip_transformations/` — models, macros, schema YAML, sources.

## How to sync (correct method)

Always use a **temporary clone + subdirectory-filter** so `dbt_project.yml` ends up at the root of `responsum-team/dbtproject`. Never run `git filter-repo` directly on the main repo — it removes the `origin` remote and destroys local history.

```bash
source .env   # loads PAT2

rm -rf /tmp/dbt-push-tmp
git clone https://github.com/elixirrjob1/cursorskills.git /tmp/dbt-push-tmp
cd /tmp/dbt-push-tmp
git filter-repo --subdirectory-filter dbt_project/drip_transformations --force
git remote add dbt-remote "https://${PAT2}@github.com/responsum-team/dbtproject.git"
git push dbt-remote main:main --force
```

After pushing, verify `dbt_project.yml` is at root — if not, dbt Cloud will error with "valid dbt project was not found".

## Common mistakes

- Running `git filter-repo --path dbt_project/drip_transformations/` on the main repo — this keeps the full path prefix, so `dbt_project.yml` ends up at `dbt_project/drip_transformations/dbt_project.yml` (wrong).
- Using `scripts/push-dbt-remote.sh` — it attempts a merge pull which causes conflicts. Use the clone method above instead.
- Triggering a dbt Cloud job immediately after pushing to `elixirrjob1/cursorskills` without syncing — the job will run against old code.

## Hash key consistency rule

All FK hashes in fact views must use the same formula as their target dim PK hashes.

DimCustomer and DimProduct PKs are computed as:
```sql
HASH(CAST(id AS VARCHAR) || '|' || 'ERP')
```

FactSales FKs must match:
```sql
HASH(COALESCE(CAST(CUSTOMER_ID AS VARCHAR), '#@#@#@#@#') || '|' || 'ERP') AS "CustomerHashFK"
HASH(COALESCE(CAST(PRODUCT_ID AS VARCHAR), '#@#@#@#@#') || '|' || 'ERP') AS "ProductHashFK"
```

If a FK mismatch is reported, check the hash formula in both the fact view and the dim view before triggering a reload.
